<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-200-187 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 543 503</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 15 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer Sciences/GE develop Japanese navy combat system.andO;(adaptation of U.S. Navy's Aegis System)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wingrove, Norman.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   General Electric Co. (Contracts)Computer Sciences Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    CSC; GE.andO;Topic:     ContractsJapanMilitary.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMPUTER SCIENCES/GE DEVELOP JAPANESE NAVY COMBAT SYSTEM 03/15/91 EL SEGUNDO,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1991 MAR 15 (NB) -- Computer Sciences and GeneralElectric are to pool resources to develop a shipboard naval combat system forthe Japanese navy.andM;Computer Sciences has signed a contract with GE to adapt software used in theUS Aegis weapons system so that it can be used with systems already employedby the Japanese navy.andM;GE is the principal contractor for the project, which will see the Aegissystem installed aboard destroyers of the Japanese Joint Maritime SelfDefence Force.andP;  Computer Sciences, in addition to providing the modifiedsoftware, will supply maintenance, with the option of future maintenance andupgrading services worth a further US$25 million over the US$7.9 million thecompany will receive under the initial 30-month contract with GE.andM;(Norman Wingrove/19910315/Press Contact: Jim Furlong, Computer Sciences Corp,andplus; 1 213 615 0311)</TEXT></DOC>